# Set Action Queue Pause State
This action will freeze either a named `Action Queue` or all queues, effectively disabling the bot from being able to perform any commands, alerts, channel point rewards etc. until the queue is resumed.

Valid States `Pause` `Resume`

![set-action-queue-pause-state.png](/set-action-queue-pause-state.png)

{.is-warning}
> If all action queues are paused, you will not be able to unpause them unless the action is set to `Always Run`
{.is-warning}

`Clear` This will purge any pending actions in the queue as the state change happens. Purging a queue can also be done separately with a `Clear Action Queue` subaction


---

## Guide - Building a global Killswitch

There are times when you may want to temporarily prevent Streamer.bot from reacting to any incoming event or command. The workflow below will set up 3 actions to exist outside the usual queue system to enable quick and easy control over the other actions Streamer.bot can perform

###### Setting up a 'Killswitch' queue

```diagram

```

Under `Settings` -> `General`, create a queue to contain your Killswitch actions. This is to ensure that it will always be ready to run when you need it to, and not have it waiting behind other pending actions

Having this action separate from the `Pause` and `Resume` actions allows you flexibility. You might want to pause actions while something important happens and then you want the queue that has built up to carry on, or you might want to purge all actions in the case of hostile raids and follow botting for example.
